{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f843a9fe-8f38-47ae-b2cc-2917f617e0e6","content":"For a **.NET Web API** project, use:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single tenant Azure AD (org accounts) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows/Negotiate authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# API with Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com\n\n# API with Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# Minimal API (default in .NET 6+)\ndotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer or cookie auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer`. Run `dotnet new webapi --help` to see all options for your installed SDK version.\n\nWould you like help scaffolding a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ce46d0c2-ee20-425c-9225-ebb8be8743ed","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/programming question rather than something specific to the codebase. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nActually, let me check if there's anything in the current directory that might give context about what framework they're working with.","outputTokens":360,"requestId":"6830:97105:4AE666C:52EEC42:69F9F697"},"id":"038aa402-2b3b-4bf6-9fa1-f63b37b2ad82","timestamp":"2026-05-05T13:54:47.340Z","parentId":"a8aa6051-b008-47c3-96f5-b4aa7093d94b"}
